Package: treeowen
Type: Package
Title: Efficient Game-Theoretic Explanations for Tree-Based Ensembles via Owen Values
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R: person("Hyunwook", "Koh",
    email = "hyunwook.koh@stonybrook.edu",
    role  = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides exact and Monte Carlo algorithms for computing Owen values
    in tree-based ensemble models, including gradient boosting machines
    (XGBoost, LightGBM) and random forests (Ranger). Owen values extend the
    Shapley value to settings where features are organized into groups,
    allocating attribution first across groups and then within each group.
    The package includes robust compatibility wrappers for model unification
    that handle version differences across xgboost (1.6 to 2.x), lightgbm
    (3.x and 4.x), ranger (0.11 to 0.16+), and treeshap (0.3 to 0.4+).
    Global importance measures and visualization tools (flat and hierarchical
    beeswarm plots) are also provided.

